==References==
*The description refers to various self-help books:
**"Sharpen the saw" is the seventh [[Wikipedia:The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People|habit of highly effective people]].
**''[[Wikipedia:Who Moved My Cheese?|Who Moved My Cheese?]]'' is a parable about reacting to change.
**''[[Wikipedia:How to Win Friends and Influence People|How to Win Friends and Influence People]]'' was one of the first best-selling self-help books.
*"I'm good enough, I'm smart enough, and doggone it, people like me." is a catchphrase of [[Wikipedia:Stuart Smalley|Stuart Smalley]].

